President Trump addressed a graduation ceremony for the Hope for Prisoners program in Las Vegas, Nevada. He praised the program for its work in helping formerly incarcerated individuals reintegrate into society and find employment. The president also spoke about criminal justice reform and the need for second chances for those who have served their time. He mentioned the case of Roger Stone, expressing his opinion that Stone has a good chance of exoneration. Trump also highlighted the strong economy and low unemployment rate, and encouraged businesses to consider hiring individuals with criminal records. He concluded his remarks by urging the graduates to seize their future and contribute to the country's national renewal.